==English==
===Etymology===
From Neapolitan Italian [[guappo]] ("dude", "stud"), a greeting borrowed from Spanish [[guapo]] ("bold", "handsome"), from Latin [[vappa]] ("flat wine", "worthless fellow").

===Noun===
'''wop''' (''plural:'' '''wops''')

#(''US slang, derogatory'') a person of [[Italian]] descent

